repair_notes: Customer reported reduced airflow and poor cooling. Diagnosed dirty air filter restricting airflow. Replaced with new high-efficiency filter, cleaned intake grille, and verified system airflow. Recommended regular filter changes every 3 months to prevent recurrence.

Furnace not heating properly, diagnosed compressor failure due to electrical overload. Replaced faulty compressor unit, checked refrigerant levels, and tested system for proper operation. Advised on periodic electrical inspections to avoid overload.
During compressor repair, found burnt run capacitor causing start issues. Replaced with new 45/5 μF capacitor, tested motor start sequence. System now operates smoothly with improved efficiency.

Thermostat showing incorrect temperature readings, calibrated using digital thermometer. Adjusted settings, replaced batteries, and cleaned dust accumulation. Verified accurate control and recommended annual calibration.
Excessive fan noise reported, diagnosed bearing wear in blower motor. Lubricated bearings, tightened loose components, and balanced fan blades. Noise reduced, advised on regular lubrication schedule.
Furnace belt slippage causing reduced airflow. Inspected for misalignment and wear, replaced worn belt, adjusted tension. System airflow restored, recommended biannual belt checks.

Window AC thermostat calibration error leading to uneven cooling. Calibrated using standard reference, optimized settings for energy efficiency, cleaned sensor. System now maintains set temperature accurately.
Clogged condensate drain line causing water leakage. Cleaned using nitrogen flush, removed algae buildup, ensured proper slope. System draining properly, recommended annual drain line maintenance.

Ductwork leakage identified in living room split AC, reducing efficiency. Located leaks using smoke test, sealed with mastic tape, improved airflow. Verified with manometer, suggested periodic duct inspections.
Dirty air filter found during duct repair, contributing to airflow issues. Replaced filter, cleaned coils, and checked system pressure. Advised on monthly filter checks in high-pollen environments.

Furnace air filter clogged, causing reduced heating efficiency. Replaced with new filter, inspected blower motor, and tested operation. Recommended filter replacement every 2 months during peak usage.

Circuit board malfunction in window AC, causing intermittent shutdowns. Diagnosed water damage and electrical shorts, replaced control board, tested all functions. System restored, advised on protecting from moisture.

Refrigerant leak detected near evaporator coil during circuit board repair. Located leak using electronic detector, repaired with brazing, recharged system to specification. Verified cooling performance and leak-free operation.

Dirty air filter in basement split AC reducing cooling capacity. Replaced filter, cleaned outdoor unit coils, checked refrigerant levels. System efficiency improved, suggested quarterly filter maintenance.

Seasonal efficiency drop noted in chiller, diagnosed dirty coils and blocked vents. Cleaned condenser coils, cleared vents, optimized thermostat settings. Performance restored, recommended biannual coil cleaning.

Central AC thermostat calibration error causing uneven cooling in lobby. Calibrated using digital reference, updated software, tested temperature accuracy. System now maintains consistent comfort levels.

Chiller showing seasonal efficiency issues, found blocked vents and dirty filters. Cleaned components, verified airflow, optimized settings. Efficiency improved, advised on regular maintenance schedule.
Excessive fan noise in ventilation system, diagnosed bearing wear and loose blades. Lubricated bearings, tightened components, balanced fan. Noise eliminated, recommended annual lubrication.

Sensor malfunction in chiller causing inaccurate temperature readings. Replaced faulty temperature sensor, calibrated system, tested under load. Accurate control restored, suggested sensor checks every 6 months.
Belt slippage in window AC blower, causing reduced airflow. Inspected for wear, replaced belt, adjusted alignment and tension. Airflow restored, advised on periodic belt inspections.

Bearing failure in furnace blower motor, diagnosed wear and lack of lubrication. Replaced bearings, lubricated moving parts, tested operation. Smooth operation achieved, recommended annual lubrication.
Dirty air filter in kitchen split AC, reducing cooling efficiency. Replaced filter, cleaned coils, checked system pressure. Efficiency restored, suggested monthly filter checks.

Thermostat calibration error in garage window AC, causing temperature fluctuations. Calibrated using reference thermometer, replaced batteries, cleaned contacts. Accurate control achieved, recommended annual calibration.

Refrigerant leak detected in heat pump evaporator coil, diagnosed corrosion. Located leak, repaired with brazing, recharged system, tested for leaks and performance. System cooling efficiently, advised on annual refrigerant checks.

Clogged condensate drain line found during refrigerant repair, causing water backup. Cleaned drain line using vacuum, removed debris, ensured proper slope. Drainage restored, recommended quarterly drain maintenance.
Seasonal efficiency drop in window AC due to dirty coils and blocked vents. Cleaned coils, cleared vents, optimized settings. Performance improved, advised on pre-season maintenance.
Compressor vibration issues in ventilation system, diagnosed loose mounting bolts. Tightened bolts, checked for internal damage, balanced load. Vibration reduced, recommended periodic bolt checks.
Condensate pump failure in furnace, diagnosed motor burnout. Replaced pump, tested float switch, cleared clogs. Proper drainage ensured, advised on annual pump inspection.
Capacitor failure in split AC, causing intermittent start issues. Replaced with new capacitor, tested electrical connections. System starts reliably, recommended capacitor check every 2 years.

Improper system sizing suspected in chiller, leading to inefficiency. Performed load calculation, adjusted settings, optimized operation. Efficiency improved, suggested future capacity assessment if issues persist.
